quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,49,"And of all things We created two mates [i.e., counterparts]; perhaps you will remember."
  51,50,"So flee to Allāh.{1} Indeed, I am to you from Him a clear warner.",footnotes:1:i.e., turn to Allāh and take refuge in Him from disbelief and sin, thereby escaping His punishment.
  51,51,"And do not make [as equal] with Allāh another deity. Indeed, I am to you from Him a clear warner."
  52,40,"Or do you, [O Muḥammad], ask of them a payment, so they are by debt burdened down?"
  52,41,"Or have they [knowledge of] the unseen, so they write [it] down?"
  52,42,"Or do they intend a plan? But those who disbelieve - they are the object of a plan."
  53,34,"And gave a little and [then] refrained?"
  53,35,"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he sees?{1}",footnotes:1:Knows that his provision will be exhausted if he spends on the poor, while Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) has promised otherwise.
  53,36,"Or has he not been informed of what was in the scriptures of Moses"
  54,25,"Has the message been sent down upon him from among us? Rather, he is an insolent liar."
  54,26,"They will know tomorrow who is the insolent liar."
  54,27,"Indeed, We are sending the she-camel as trial for them, so watch them and be patient.{1}",footnotes:1:This and the following verse are an address to Ṣāliḥ (upon him be peace).
  55,19,"He released the two seas,{1} meeting [one another];",footnotes:1:Two bodies of water or two sea waters of distinct characteristics.
  55,20,"Between them is a barrier so neither of them transgresses."
  55,21,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  56,10,"And the forerunners, the forerunners{1} -",footnotes:1:The words can also be understood as a complete sentence, i.e., "The forerunners [in good deeds] are the forerunners [in entering Paradise]."
  56,11,"Those are the ones brought near [to Allāh]"
  56,12,"In the Gardens of Pleasure,"
  57,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and earth exalts Allāh,{1} and He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise.",footnotes:1:By praising Him and declaring Him far above and beyond any failure or imperfection.
  57,2,"His is the dominion of the heavens and earth. He gives life and causes death, and He is over all things competent."
  57,3,"He is the First{1} and the Last,{2} the Ascendant{3} and the Intimate,{4} and He is, of all things, Knowing.",footnotes:1:Before whom nothing existed.  Also, He who is supreme, foremost or uppermost.,footnotes:2:Enduring eternally when nothing else remains.,footnotes:3:Nothing being above Him.  Another meaning is \"the Apparent,\" i.e., evident through His creation and revelation.,footnotes:4:Nothing being nearer than Him by way of His knowledge.  Another meaning is \"the Unapparent,\" i.e., concealed from man's physical senses.
